\n< Guild Master >Hey Erika. How are you feeling?

\n< Erika >Give me a more clever greeting. Can't you see that
I'm fine?

\n< Guild Master >Looks like you've overcome the hurdle. Quite
impressive, quite impressive.
\n< Erika >...Was it really that bad?

\n< Guild Master >Your right arm was blown off from the root. Your
whole body, inside and out, is in tatters. If it
weren't for you, you would have died long ago.
\n< Guild Master >Your vitality is on par with that of a monster.
\n< Erika >That damn Minotaur...
\n< Guild Master >Here you go.
\n< Erika >Ouch, don't throw it. What is it? A ring...?

\n< Guild Master >It's Ricott's ring. It came out of his stomach.
Isn't that what you were looking for?
\n< Erika >Ah... So, everything is settled then.

\n< Guild Master >We're just finishing up now. If we leave it alone,
monsters will come to feast on the dead flesh.

\n< Guild Master >We'll divide it up and dispose of it by
incineration. We don't have enough manpower. We
also need to dispose of the thieves' corpses.
\n< Erika >...So, what about that small one?

\n< Guild Master >I issued a travel permit. By now, you should have
arrived in the eastern town.
\n< Erika >I see. Ugh...
\n< Guild Master >Were you planning to come along?

\n< Erika >Is it bad? You're worried, right... Especially
since it's such a town as our destination.

\n< Guild Master >You lost your right arm because of that kindness
of yours, didn't you? How about reflecting on it a
little?

\n< Erika >I pushed through until I lost my right arm. It
would be stupid to back down now, wouldn't it?

\n< Guild Master >...So, you're saying you have no intention of
retiring.

\n< Erika >I don't know any other way of living... Unless
there's a weirdo who would marry a one-armed
woman, then it's a different story.
\n< Guild Master >Your chances are slim.

\n< Erika >Don't you have any decency?! Who do you think you
are!

\n< Erika >Ugh, just go home already! Don't you have work to
do?!

\n< Erika >If you keep emitting your old age stench, even
medicine won't cure it!
\n< Guild Master >Ah, even without being told, I'll go home...
\n< Erika >What is it?
\n< Guild Master >Did you drink the medicine I gave you?

\n< Erika >Tch, so you came to ask about that. You're really
such a worrywart, aren't you?

\n< Erika >I drank it. Every last drop. Before I lost my
right arm.

\n< Guild Master >Well, that's good. With that injury, I can't make
you drink it now.

\n< Erika >It's not good. I had a fucking terrible
experience. Besides, even if I drank it, I've
never had any positive results...

\n< Erika >Anyway, well, I guess it'll be fine. They were all
fucking losers with small cocks anyway.
\n< Erika >...Thank you.
\n< Guild Master >Ah.

\n< Guild Master >Ah, even without being told, I'm planning to take
my leave soon. But before I go, I'll give you
this.
\n< Erika >What is it?
\n< Guild Master >It's medicine. You know what's inside, right?

\n< Guild Master >It's a powerful medicine. I couldn't make you
drink it until you woke up.
\n< Erika >....

\n< Guild Master >If you drink it before you're capable, it will be
effective. Drink it as soon as possible.
\n< Erika >If it's ready? It's been another week, hasn't it?
\n< Guild Master >....
\n< Erika >...Ah, sorry, sorry. Don't make that kind of face.

\n< Erika >If something happens, you'll take care of it
yourself. I know a good doctor.

\n< Erika >Seriously! There's no way those weaklings would
stand a chance against me!
\n< Guild Master >...Ah, I hope so. I really hope so.

\n< Guild Master >Well then, I'll go to work this time. Don't walk
around too much, okay?
\n< Erika >Hey, go home, go home!
\n< Erika >...Haaa...Ah...It hurts...

\n< Erika >Defeating the bad guys and solving everything,
happily ever after. It's like a story, isn't it?

\n< Erika >But well... Happiness and sadness are in a 6:4
ratio... Let's just barely call it a happy
ending...
\n< Erika >Hey... Serena... thank you...
